        <p class="subheading">
            <b>Measured Environmental Impact</b>
        </p>
        <div id="meit">
            <p>
                The measure of carbon dioxide sequestration by <span style=font-weight:bold;color:rgb(157,107,15)>Live Oak Trees</span> and <span style=font-weight:bold;color:rgb(157,107,15)>Chinkapin Oak</span> Trees is presented in the table below.
            </p>
            <p>
                Over many years, even one tree can have a very significant impact in reducing the Urban Heat Island Effect through carbon sequestration.
            </p>
        </div>
        <table>
            <tr class="table_heading">
                <td> Type of Tree </td>
                <td> Impact Over 1 Year </td>
                <td> Impact Over 20 Years </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td> Live Oak  </td>
                <td> CO2 equivalent of carbon 232.93 lbs </td>
                <td> CO2 equivalent of carbon 8,115.71 lbs  </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td> Chinkapin Oak </td>
                <td> CO2 equivalent of carbon 109.73 lbs </td>
                <td> CO2 equivalent of carbon 4,021.90 lbs </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
